The South African Football Association has suspended all soccer matches due to the coronavirus pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The financial impact of the coronavirus in sports is expected to spiral to millions of rands as the virus forces sports events around the world to be cancelled or postponed. The Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa's advisor Walter Mokoena says government is fully aware of the potential losses in revenue. "Sadly there is millions of rands in terms of loss income of sponsorship, broadcast contents rights and etc. So all the efforts are of how government can come in and assist," Mokoena said. READ: Rand plunges on coronavirus fears Currently, South Africa has 150 confirmed COVID-19 cases and the government says the number of infections is likely to rise. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.